H0.text: What is the median of 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9 and 25. 5

H1.text: What is the median of 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9 and 25. 7

H2.text: What is the median of 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9 and 25. 1

H3.text: What is the median of 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9 and 25. 6

A4.text: The median of a finite list of numbers is the 'middle' number, when those numbers are listed in order from smallest to greatest.

A5.text: If the data set has an odd number of observations, the middle one is selected (after arranging in ascending order).
